---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Share from "../components/Share.astro";
import Tooltip from "../components/Tooltip.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
import Resource from "../components/Resource.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <section class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 sm:py-24 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-base-content/60 mb-4">
      The movement for a prosperous New Zealand
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-tight">
      Tax <span
        class="bg-linear-to-r from-amber-500 to-yellow-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
        >wealth</span
      >, <br />not <span
        class="bg-linear-to-r from-emerald-600 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
        >work</span
      >.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg sm:text-xl text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
      New Zealand taxes the wages of nurses, teachers and tradies but barely
      touches the fortunes that grow quietly in property and shares. Everyone
      should contribute their fair share to invest in our future.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-start sm:flex-row gap-3">
      <a href="#solution" class="btn btn-neutral">What's the solution?</a>
      <a href="#future" class="btn btn-primary">What could we fund?</a>
      <a href="#involved" class="btn">How to help</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-base-200 border-y border-base-300">
    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The problem</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
        Most Kiwis earn their living through work, and pay tax on every dollar
        earned. But income from things like capital gains on investment
        property, large inheritances, and share portfolio profits is untouched.
        The result is a system that leans heaviest on those who can least afford
        it and starves us of the means to invest in our future.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-base-content/80">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">→</span>
          <span>Wage earners shoulder an unfair share of the tax take.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">→</span>
          <span
            >NZ is the only <Tooltip
              title="The Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development — a group of 38 mostly high-income countries that share economic policy and data."
              >OECD</Tooltip
            > country with no capital gains tax, no inheritance tax, and no wealth
            tax.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">→</span>
          <span
            >Housing is treated more like a money maker than a necessity.</span
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    id="solution"
    class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto scroll-mt-16"
  >
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The solution</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
      Wealth should be taxed like work. A good start is a <span
        class="font-bold underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4"
        >land value tax</span
      >. It's a modest annual charge on the value of land, not the buildings or
      work built on top of it.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <Card title="A tax that's hard to dodge">
        Land can't be hidden offshore, moved, or disguised in a trust. Taxing it
        lets us ease the load on the wages and effort of ordinary Kiwis.
      </Card>
      <Card title="Cheaper homes, less speculation">
        A holding cost on land takes the easy money out of land-banking and
        property portfolios. It nudges house prices down and frees up land to
        build on.
      </Card>
      <Card title="Investment that builds, not hoards">
        When land stops being the best investment, capital flows into
        businesses, jobs and innovation.
      </Card>
      <Card title="Billions to invest in our future">
        Even a modest rate would raise billions a year to fund the things a
        growing country needs.
      </Card>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    id="future"
    class="bg-base-200 border-y border-base-300 scroll-mt-16"
  >
    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        A future worth <span
          class="bg-linear-to-r from-emerald-600 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
          >building</span
        >
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
        This isn't about punishing success or pulling anyone down. It's about
        everyone contributing their fair share to invest in the future:
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <Card title="Warm, dry, affordable homes">
          Treat housing as somewhere to live, not just an asset to flip.
        </Card>
        <Card title="Healthcare without the wait">
          Shorter queues, GP visits people can afford, and a system that catches
          problems early instead of expensively late.
        </Card>
        <Card title="Schools and skills that lift wages">
          Every kid and every worker with a genuine shot. Skills and
          education are what raise productivity and pay over the long run.
        </Card>
        <Card title="Investment in the industries of tomorrow">
          Back research, tech and clean energy so we grow the high-value
          industries that create good jobs for the decades ahead.
        </Card>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Share />

  <section class="bg-base-200 border-y border-base-300 scroll-mt-16">
    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Learn more</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
        You're not alone in thinking this. Voices across the world have been
        making the case for years. Here's where to start:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-8 space-y-8">
        <Resource
          href="https://www.opportunity.org.nz/tax-reset"
          title="Opportunity Land Value Tax Policy"
        >
          Opportunity Party - 1.75% Land Value Tax to fund a Citizen's Income.
        </Resource>
        <Resource
          href="https://thespinoff.co.nz/the-bulletin/27-04-2023/ird-report-reveals-fundamental-unfairness-of-how-the-wealthy-are-taxed/"
          title="‘Fundamental unfairness’ of how the wealthy are taxed"
        >
          IRD Report - write up by The Spinoff shows how the wealthy aren't paying their fair share.
        </Resource>
        <Resource
          href="https://archive.is/bkS21"
          title="The Case for a Land Value Tax"
        >
          FT - The case for a land value tax in the US/UK rings true in NZ too.
        </Resource>
        <Resource
          href="https://www.youtube.com/@garyseconomics"
          title="Gary's Economics"
        >
          UK Movement - ex-Citi trader Gary Stevenson on why wealth inequality
          is the story of our time.
        </Resource>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-base-300">
    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">More coming soon</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base-content/70">
        This is just the start. Check back as the movement grows.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base-content/70">
        Got ideas on how to further the cause or spread the message? Reach out
        at
        <a href="mailto:hello@twnw.nz" class="link link-primary"
          >hello@twnw.nz</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
